{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper and set aside.","Place sugar in mixing bowl then mill <nobr>4 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place 30 g pistachio nuts in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place remaining 60 g pistachio nuts and 30 g reserved ground sugar in mixing bowl and mill <nobr>15 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Add rice flour and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Throughly clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert<\/strong> <strong>butterfly<\/strong> <strong>whisk<\/strong> <strong>.<\/strong> Place egg whites in mixing bowl and whisk <nobr>2 min\/37°C\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>.","With butterfly whisk still in place, whip <nobr>3 min\/37°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>, slowly add remaining reserved ground sugar through hole in mixing bowl lid, 1 tablespoon at a time, until soft peaks form and meringue is glossy. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add vanilla and reserved pistachio and sugar mixture then combine <nobr>4 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then repeat <nobr>4 sec\/\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Dot 10 teaspoons of biscuit mixture on 1 prepared baking tray leaving approx. 6 cm space between each, then top with a sprinkle of reserved crushed pistachios. Repeat with remaining biscuit mixture and second prepared baking tray then garnish with remaining crushed pistachio nuts.","Bake for 9 minutes (180°C) or until browned around the edges. Dust with icing sugar while still warm, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely (approx. 20 minutes) before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["80 g granulated sugar","90 g pistachio nuts","30 g rice flour","2 egg whites","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","2 tbsp icing sugar, for dusting"]}],"id":"r146864","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-cjf5eW8VxYM\/XZWrJAIkDxI\/AAAAAAAAf